article.headline: Vermont 83, Binghamton 53
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. (AP) -- Taylor Coppenrath scored a season-high 39 points and grabbed 12 rebounds as Vermont beat Binghamton 83-53 Sunday in the America East Conference opener for both. Coppenrath, the nation's fourth-leading scorer entering the game with a 23.8 average, was 12-for-17 from the field and 15-for-17 from the free throw line in his most impressive performance since scoring a career-high 43 in Vermont's win over Maine in last season's conference tournament championship game. He scored six points and had two assists in a 19-2 run to close out the first half as the two-time defending conference champion Catamounts (3-2) took a 36-24 lead. Freshman Ryan Schneider added a season-high 14 points for Vermont, shooting 4-for-9 from 3-point range, and Germain Mopa Njila added six points, three assists and eight rebounds. The Catamounts outrebounded the Bearcats 40-36 and committed just eight turnovers. Troy Hailey had 17 points for Binghamton (2-6), which shot 32 percent from the field, including 4-for-27 from beyond the arc. Nick Billings had 10 points and five rebounds for the Bearcats.
